body: Halifax is VIA Rail's busiest East Station and ninth in terms of visitor traffic. Recently renovated, elements of sustainable development and accessibility have been incorporated into the heritage architecture.
title: HLFX - HALIFAX STATION

body: The terminus for TorontoKingston commuter trains and a major stop on the TorontoMontral and TorontoOttawa routes, Kingston station welcomes an average of 20 trains per day, making it VIA Rails sixth-busiest station.
title: KGON - KINGSTON STATION

body: The last major stop before the TorontoSarnia train terminus and the TorontoWindsor train terminus, London station is VIA Rails fourth-busiest station.
title: LNDN - LONDON STATION

body: As the major railway station for the second-largest port in Canada , Montral Central Station played an important role in connecting Canadian cities. VIA Rails second-busiest station is also the main transportation hub for the Island of Montral, providing connections with regional and local trains, buses, and the subway system. Moreover, Montral Central Station, owned by Cominar, is connected to Montrals famous underground city, a pedestrian network spread over 32 km.
title: MTRL - Montral Central Station

body: In 2000, VIA Rails Ottawa station, built by famed Canadian architect John Cresswell Parkin, was named one of the top 500 buildings produced in Canada during the last millennium. It is currently our most accessible station and one of our 10 main stations in terms of visitor traffic.
title: OTTW - OTTAWA STATION

body: The first train station built in the province of Qubec, the Gare du Palaiss chateau-style architecture is similar to that of the Chteau Frontenac. The gare du Palais is the fifth-busiest station in terms of visitors.
title: QBEC - Gare du Palais  Qubec City

body: Torontos Union Station, owned by the city of Toronto, is VIA Rails busiest station, welcoming more than two million visitors per year. Canadas largest and most opulent station is a major hub for intercity travel. It is located in the heart of the city and features a market, restaurants, ongoing arts and cultural events, boutiques, a hair salon, and much more.
title: TRTO - Union Station - Toronto

body: Vancouvers Pacific Central Station is the western terminus of the Great Western Way route. It is also a junction for trains heading to the United States.
title: VCVR - Pacific Central Station  Vancouver

body: Located near the Canada-US border, Windsor train station is the western terminus of the Quebec CityWindsor Corridor. In terms of visitors, it is the seventh-busiest station.
title: WDON - WINDSOR STATION

body: Designed by Warren and Wetmore, the architects behind New York Citys famous Grand Central Terminal, Union Station is the finest example of a Beaux Artsstyle railway station in Canada. It is VIA Rails tenth-busiest station and has significant heritage value.
title: WNPG - UNION STATION WINNIPEG
